edu.ncsu.csc216.get_outdoors.util

Class SortedLinkedList<E extends java.lang.Comparable<E>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.ncsu.csc216.get_outdoors.util.SortedLinkedList<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - the element type to be stored in the list.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    SortedList<E>

    public class SortedLinkedList<E extends java.lang.Comparable<E>>
extends java.lang.Object
implements SortedList<E>
    Implementation of a SortedList with a LinkedList as its underlying data structure. Elements stored in the list must be Comparable types, as their order in the list is determined by the return value of their compareTo() methods, relative to other elements in the list.
    Author:
    demills

      • hashCode

        public int hashCode()
        Generates and returns an integer hash of the "head" Node. This value is calculated recursively, by calling head.hashCode(), which itself will call next.hashCode() for its next Node. In this way, every Node in the list will contribute to the final value returned here.
        Overrides:
        hashCode in class java.lang.Object
        Returns:
        returns an integer hash of the SortedLinkedList.
